	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is a rather comprehensive guide, and i remember when i just started out i'd of had no idea what you were talking about, so if you seem to be in the same situation as i was, play the game a little and ask people to help you, it is better to be talked with than to.<BR>
<BR>
Also this seems to be all about level 10 to 20 grouping (other than the rat/bunnie/gnoll pup killing segment)<BR>
	YOU ARE A WIZARD YOU DON'T HAVE TO GROUP<BR>
i find groups to be fun, but soloing is much better experiance.<BR>
<BR>
there is a tactic called &quot;kiting&quot; this means getting a spell cast upon you that makes you run faster, casting at the mob, running and gaining distance, then casting again, and repeat til dead.<BR>
Wizards can kill things faster than any other class, so we accomplish this quickly.<BR>
<BR>
I am currently level 28 and when i don't group i average a bubble of xp an hour without the risk of death, if groups don't work for you, solo, it's fun.<BR>
<BR>
also next level, level 29 i get spell BONDS OF FORCE which makes the mobs hit go extreamly slower, so you don't even need to be faster.<BR>
<BR>
By the way, i suggest NEVER MEELEING past level 16 unless you need a quick 20 points of damage, which is very rare, for this simple fact- if you meditate you can get enough mana for much more damage than your meeleing for, example:<BR>
if i meele i do 12 damage a round at best, a round is around a second, so in 10 seconds i will do around 50damage, that is with a very nice weapon. but in 10 seconds if i meditate i can cast a 110 damage spell, or in 15 seconds a 180 damage spell.<BR>
now you tell me which is better.<BR>
<BR>
a very good guide on low level grouping though, and a nice guide on how not to lose all your little wizard hp and get killed<BR>
<BR>
Leanid Flaymaster  Vallon Zek
				</font>
			</td>

